{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0128jrD8yP11ZCT4UqepXaeE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Elasticsearch is using SSL for the HTTP endpoint. So the backend is HTTPS. This means:\n1. The ingress needs to proxy to HTTPS backend (not HTTP)\n2. The ingress itself also needs TLS termination for `es.example.com`\n\nFor the ingress to work with an HTTPS backend, I need to annotate the ingress with:\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/backend-protocol: \"HTTPS\"` to tell nginx to use HTTPS to communicate with the backend\n\nBut there's also the matter of TLS termination at the ingress level. I need:\n1. A TLS certificate for `es.example.com` (I'll generate a self-signed one)\n2. A Kubernetes secret to store that certificate\n3. An Ingress resource configured to terminate TLS for `es.example.com`, proxy HTTPS traffic to the `es-http` service, and handle HTTP-to-HTTPS redirection\n\nLet me start by generating a self-signed certificate for `es.example.com`, then create the secret and ingress resource. First, I should check what certificates Elasticsearch already has set up.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":989,"cache_read_input_tokens":30756,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":989},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0c2c1618-a165-493b-8421-e42b974c88a3","uuid":"48ca3f58-99df-4bc4-aea8-697dcc8ca030","request_id":"req_011CcfpxCEnqcwFP55L5NAoc"}
