{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JWGY73g1Mbw3bDxmV7w4Kc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working correctly. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **Labeled the control-plane node** with `ingress-ready=true` — the ingress-nginx controller pod required this label selector to schedule.\n\n2. **Generated a self-signed TLS certificate** for `es.example.com` and stored it as a Kubernetes Secret `es-ingress-tls` in the `elasticsearch` namespace.\n\n3. **Created an Ingress resource** (`elasticsearch-https`) with:\n   - `ingressClassName: nginx` — uses the nginx ingress class\n   - TLS termination via the `es-ingress-tls` secret for `es.example.com`\n   - `backend-protocol: HTTPS` — required because Elasticsearch itself uses TLS/xpack security\n   - `proxy-ssl-verify: off` — skips verification of the backend's self-signed cert\n   - `ssl-redirect: true` + `force-ssl-redirect: true` — HTTP requests get a `308 Permanent Redirect` to HTTPS\n\n**Verified results:**\n- `https://es.example.com` → returns Elasticsearch API (cluster status: **green**, 3/3 nodes)\n- `http://es.example.com` → `308 Permanent Redirect`, plain HTTP does not succeed"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":583,"cache_read_input_tokens":36139,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":583},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0c2c1618-a165-493b-8421-e42b974c88a3","uuid":"5d7e59c3-974f-4721-8174-40c83f9c3d99","request_id":"req_011Ccfq32VntzRQyrJFMr24r"}
